“Half of my life I grew up in Japan, half in Hawaii. Different parts of my life I’ve competed in that venue. Not everybody gets to say, you know, I represent a country I grew up in, but also a country my parents grew up in as well.” - #SakuraKokumai

For Karateka Sakura Kokumai, joining #TeamUSA at the #Tokyo2020 Games is symbolic of her own storied journey — where her childhoods in both Japan and America reach full circle at the Games.

Watch Sakura's film now on IGTV.

#RalphLauren #RLxTeamUSA #TeamUSA #TokyoOlympics #Olympics

Join us in our support of @StonewallFoundation via the link in bio.

#RalphLauren #RLPride

node.text:
To mark the 20th anniversary of our #PinkPony campaign, we invited a cast of global luminaries to share wisdom they learned during their cancer journeys. Their stories of hope, strength, and love continue to inspire us. 

“Hope is knowing that being diagnosed does not mean that your life is over. There's still life to live, there are still things for you to fight for,” said Ericka Hart (@IHartEricka), a Black, queer, femme writer, breast cancer survivor, highly-acclaimed speaker, and award-winning sexuality educator.

While in conversation, Dr. Maya Rockeymoore Cummings (@MayaRCummings), author, speaker, and social entrepreneur with a mission to drive society toward inclusion, speaks to the importance of love in the fight against cancer. “Love is a never-ending chain. One that you receive and one that you give all the time.” 

Discover more from our Pink Pony campaign via the link in bio.

#RalphLauren

For this year’s #PinkPony campaign, we invited a cast of global luminaries to share how love shaped their cancer journeys.

Desirée A. H. Walker, a two-time breast cancer victor, health educator, support group facilitator, and cancer patient advocate said: “Love is seeing yourself and knowing you’re worthy."

Dr. Rosa Nouvini, MD, Medical Oncologist at MSK Ralph Lauren Center added: "Love is the greatest source of hope."

She explained that love from family and support from one's community made all the difference when fighting cancer.

“One piece of advice that I would give someone that's newly diagnosed is to not be afraid to ask for help," Nouvini noted. 

Discover the full Pink Pony campaign via the link in bio.

#RalphLauren
